Oh dear, 
@PolariPrize
. Anyone targeted or harmed by this vicious movement knows that “I told you so” are the most pointless, emptiest words. But I certainly did “tell them”. Having been excluded from the prize, for many years, because of how it would all kick off, I did try to talk, repeatedly, to the organisers, explaining that this was not the way to go, and that it would come back one day and bite them soundly on the arse. It has of course, and the prize looks now like it will collapse. 
@JohnBoyneBooks
, who is a personal friend, but who I would support even if he were the ambassador for eating crisps on trains, is worth millions of any of those whingeing idiots that dare to think they can hold the prize to ransom by the usual bullying and smear tactics. Of course, they will ‘win’. But really the win belongs to those of us that could not give a damn about being censored by these pricks any longer. Watch this space for a further announcement. Lesbians and gay men deserve our own space, including in the literary prize world…

